"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ba8251",
"children":[
"Typical findings of chronic plaque psoriasis are erythema, scaling, and induration on the extensor surfaces, scalp, ears, intertriginous folds, and genitalia. The nails may be pitted, thickened, or yellow with subungual debris and may be the only manifestation of psoriasis. Psoriatic arthritis and spondylitis may coexist in approximately 25% of patients."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f8f89f",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Psoriasis is exacerbated by systemic glucocorticoids, lithium, antimalarial drugs, tetracyclines, β-blockers, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs",
"children":[
"NSAIDs"
]
},
","
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"angiotensin-converting enzyme",
"children":[
"ACE"
]
},
" inhibitors."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s79_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s79_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0b783a",
"children":[
"Smoking cessation is recommended for all patients; smoking worsens psoriasis, and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"coronary artery disease",
"children":[
"CAD"
]
},
" is common among patients with psoriasis."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"90ded1",
"children":[
"Patients with localized disease:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"2bce4f",
"children":[
"topical glucocorticoids for limited, localized plaques"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"8af971",
"children":[
"topical vitamin D analogues as monotherapy or in combination with topical glucocorticoids"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b6e64f",
"children":[
"Patients with skin involvement of greater than 10% body surface area, psoriatic arthritis, or psoriasis recalcitrant to topical treatments should receive:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f1bcb5",
"children":[
"phototherapy"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"db1fa6",
"children":[
"methotrexate, acitretin, or cyclosporine"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ded5b3",
"children":[
"Patients receiving systemic glucocorticoids or cyclosporine are at risk for acute erythrodermic or pustular flares with sudden cessation of medication. ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Erythroderma is a dermatologic emergency because patients are at high risk for infection as well as electrolyte abnormalities secondary to fluid loss."
]
}
]
},
